"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"**CT Markets Pro User: Each STX block is somehow recorded on the BTC blockchain. How much block space does this take? What is recorded?**\\n\\n**MC:** You can [check](https://explorer.stacks.co/block/0x26fb4b1c7be1fb29e2e4d11bf9ba1db9f5dfdff00fac9582dea0472bba068532?chain=mainnet) this publicly! All of the BTC transactions are showing a size of 352 Bytes. The system’s state settles on Bitcoin — creating a new Stacks block entails sending a well-formed Bitcoin transaction that records the hash of a Stacks block and where it attaches to the blockchain. Settling the system on Bitcoin grants Stacks novel security properties not seen in other blockchains — it leverages the security of Bitcoin to guarantee that all Stacks forks are public and to help to bootstrap Stacks nodes identify the canonical Stacks fork and find Stacks blocks they have not yet downloaded.\",\"timestamp\":1639127289,\"title\":\"He mentioned the achievements of bilateral cooperation thanks to the event, including the launch of the China-Russia Mathematics Center.\"},\"digest\":\"L7zEJ-OxkEfMmGTJpL4nymsN3GkIf0X2z4k_PNGsjus\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x9eB6C10b208F81a8e370434A1E29071B354a4331\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"RNvc4zqOIqA-DkuezeHfGsxfI70ufb7WDKH_em9sDUg\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"fSVc2N8kP6L0vKjGvg51VB8lV1vZSG96cDOU4sFFHh8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"QsEUzF8n0Vmhog_0a7pRbPesWN87h0l6nxrOOwfG8ebGKp5Aj-TjhVEAIPKRSx9KTF1hID3vTQwi42W8JamNEg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x275942d048186d7c9b32edbffa6902c77f554698f98c53e5dca124b97bd0f5493d732272e4c82d1ff5b5a5c625a59653bac83af4bfd61fb41d329b0f06b6685d1b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"RNvc4zqOIqA-DkuezeHfGsxfI70ufb7WDKH_em9sDUg\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"fSVc2N8kP6L0vKj